          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/edpt-200" class="program-course-title">
              EDPT 200 Integrating Educational Technology in Classrooms (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-24174" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Educational&amp;Counselling Psych (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Ed Psych &amp; Couns (Media)              : The course is designed to help practicing and future teachers integrate technology (e.g. web-based resources, hypermedia, digital video) in their daily teaching practices. It is a practical, hands-on course that is grounded in constructivist learning theory. The participants will learn by engaging in authentic tasks in a project-based learning environment.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Sam Bruzzese (Fall)                  Sam Bruzzese (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Also offered through Continuing Education and Summer Studies</li>
              <li>Not open to students who have taken or are taking   EDEC 262.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/edpt-204" class="program-course-title">
              EDPT 204 Educational Media 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-24176" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Educational&amp;Counselling Psych (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Ed Psych &amp; Couns (Media)              : Educational Media 1 is the "gateway" course for educational media. It reviews audio-visual education and emphasizes the rationale for audio-visual materials in education, and the underlying principles in their design, production and effective use.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Offered through Continuing Education</li>
              <li>Restriction(s): Not open to students who have taken or are taking EDEC 262.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                </ul>
      
      
                <h4>Electives (15 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>15 credits chosen from any of the University's course offerings to contribute to the student's academic proficiency and professional preparation.</p>
    
      
      
            </div>

    
  
  <div class="disclaimer">Faculty of Education&mdash;2014-2015 (last updated Feb. 18, 2014) (<a href="/study/2014-2015/disclaimer">disclaimer</a>)</div>
  </div> <!-- /.node -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
